<br>
YES, PEOPLE DIED. PEOPLE DIE EVERY @#%$<b></b>ING DAY. DO I SEE YOU LIGHTING CANDLES FOR THEM? No, I do not. Because you do not show any compassion unless something happens in your back yard, I really don't think anything of this sentiment is worth jack sh<b></b>it. I find it almost hilarious regarding the levels of moronic "patriotism" Americans will rise to. It's such a load of ego-inflated crap. And no, for you racist bitches, I'm not in the middle east: I'm Canadian. Cue unfunny, cliche "Oh, that explains it!" jokes. Anyway, get a damn brain and either take things like this all the way or don't post them at all. Do you care about the people who are dying right now, this very second in Pakistan, whether or not they're guilty? I know I sure as hell don't care. So I don't post things about the people who died near me. Unless you're going to care just as much about all sides of an issue, don't jump into it. <br>
<br>
Also, most people take things too seriously and need to learn to be a little bit more like Dwarkarn. Is something funny? Then laugh. Why does it matter if it's in bad taste? It's funny. Period. Get a sense of humour, relax, wake up. If you live in a bubble you're going to have quite the shi<b></b>tty life, my friends.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, <br>
