I can somewhat relate to your comments. Days after the destruction of the WTC towers I could count well over a hundred cars with American flags flying high. At work, I made the comment that this country is full of &quot;fair weather fans&quot; and bandwagoners. I was labeled as un-American in the eyes of many people that I thought would understand my comments. In my opinion, the only true American patriots are the ones that flew the flags *before* the incident occurred (hell, even people that owned one). No one bothered to ask if I was one of those people (I am).<br>
<br>
In other news... these days on my way to work I'm lucky if I see three cars with flags *anywhere* (bumper stickers included). How very American of us.<br>
<br>
